results.name: Decimal expansion of the base-2 logarithm of Otter's rooted tree constant.
comment: Storing an arbitrary unlabeled tree with n nodes takes an information-theoretic minimum of kn + O(log n) bits, where k = 1.56... is this constant. (This holds for either rooted or unrooted trees.)
